{"cursor":"3132","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nA 'tosyl' group (abbreviated Ts or Tos) is\nCH 3C 6H 4SO 2. This group is usually\nderived from the compound 4-toluenesulfonyl chloride,\nCH 3C 6H 4SO 2Cl, which forms esters and\namides of toluenesulfonic or tosylic acid. The para orientation illustrated (p-\ntoluenesulfonyl) is most common, and by convention tosyl refers to the p-\ntoluenesulfonyl group.\n\n'Tosylate' refers to the anion of p-toluenesulfonic acid\n(CH 3C 6H 4SO 3− ) and\nit is abbreviated as TsO − , or it may refer to esters of p-\ntoluenesulfonic acid.\n","linknr":122,"url":"Tosyl","recorded":1362512258,"links":25,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Sulfonyl groups","Leaving groups","Sulfonate esters"],"headings":["Applications","References","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Tosyl.png/175px-Tosyl.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/TolterodineSynthesis.png/400px-TolterodineSynthesis.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["iron(iii_chloride"]],"members":[],"related":["4-Toluenesulfonyl_chloride","Toluenesulfonic_acid","Tosylic_acid","Arene_substitution_patterns","Ester","SN2_reaction","Protecting_group","Organic_synthesis","Tolterodine","Phenol","Alcohol","Diisopropylamine","Organic_reduction","Sodium_borohydride","Friedel-Crafts_alkylation","P-cresol","Iron(III)_chloride","Sodium_hydroxide","Triethylamine","Nucleophilic_displacement","Diisopropylamine","Tartaric_acid","Tosylic_acid","Sulfonyl_group"]}